In this Constitution, unless the context otherwise requires, the following
expressions have the meanings hereby respectively assigned to them, that is to say\xe2\x80\x94
(1) \xe2\x80\x9cagricultural income\xe2\x80\x9d means agricultural income as defined for the purposes of the enactments relating to Indian income-tax;
(2) \xe2\x80\x9can Anglo-Indian\xe2\x80\x9d means a person whose father or any of whose other male progenitors in the male line is or was of European descent but who is domiciled within the territory of India and is or was born within such territory of parents habitually resident therein and not established there for temporary purposes only;
(3) \xe2\x80\x9carticle\xe2\x80\x9d means an article of this Constitution;
(4) \xe2\x80\x9cborrow\xe2\x80\x9d includes the raising of money by the grant of annuities, and \xe2\x80\x9cloan\xe2\x80\x9d shall be construed accordingly;
(5) \xe2\x80\x9cclause\xe2\x80\x9d means a clause of the article in which the expression occurs;
(6) \xe2\x80\x9ccorporation tax\xe2\x80\x9d means any tax on income, so far as that tax is payable by companies and is a tax in the case of which the following conditions are fulfilled:\xe2\x80\x94
(a) that it is not chargeable in respect of agricultural income;
(b) that no deduction in respect of the tax paid by companies is, by any enactments which may apply to the tax, authorised to be made from dividends payable by the companies to individuals;
(c) that no provision exists for taking the tax so paid into account in computing for the purposes
of Indian income-tax the total income of individuals receiving such dividends, or in computing the
Indian income-tax payable by, or refundable to, such individuals;
(7) \xe2\x80\x9ccorresponding Province\xe2\x80\x9d, \xe2\x80\x9ccorresponding Indian State\xe2\x80\x9d or \xe2\x80\x9ccorresponding State\xe2\x80\x9d means in cases of doubt such Province, Indian State or State as may be determined by the President to be the corresponding Province, the corresponding Indian State or the corresponding State, as the case may be, for the particular purpose in question;
(8) \xe2\x80\x9cdebt\xe2\x80\x9d includes any liability in respect of any obligation to repay capital sums by way of
annuities and any liability under any guarantee, and \xe2\x80\x9cdebt charges\xe2\x80\x9d shall be construed accordingly;
(9) \xe2\x80\x9cestate duty\xe2\x80\x9d means a duty to be assessed on or by reference to the principal value, ascertained in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed by or under laws made by Parliament or the Legislature of a State relating to the duty, of all property passing upon death or deemed, under the provisions of the said laws, so to pass;
(10) \xe2\x80\x9cexisting law\xe2\x80\x9d means any law, Ordinance, order, bye-law, rule or regulation passed or made before the commencement of this Constitution by any Legislature, authority or person having power to make such a law, Ordinance, order, bye-law, rule or regulation;
(11) \xe2\x80\x9cFederal Court\xe2\x80\x9d means the Federal Court constituted under the Government of India Act, 1935;
(12) \xe2\x80\x9cgoods\xe2\x80\x9d includes all materials, commodities, and articles;
(13) \xe2\x80\x9cguarantee\xe2\x80\x9d includes any obligation undertaken before the commencement of this Constitution
to make payments in the event of the profits of an undertaking falling short of a specified amount;
(14) \xe2\x80\x9cHigh Court\xe2\x80\x9d means any Court which is deemed for the purposes of this Constitution to be a High Court for any State and includes\xe2\x80\x94
(a) any Court in the territory of India constituted or reconstituted under this Constitution as a High Court, and
(b) any other Court in the territory of India which may be declared by Parliament by law to be a High Court for all or any of the purposes of this Constitution;
(15) \xe2\x80\x9cIndian State\xe2\x80\x9d means any territory which the Government of the Dominion of India recognised as such a State;
(16) \xe2\x80\x9cPart\xe2\x80\x9d means a Part of this Constitution;
(17) \xe2\x80\x9cpension\xe2\x80\x9d means a pension, whether contributory or not, of any kind whatsoever payable to or in respect of any person, and includes retired pay so payable; a gratuity so payable and any sum or sums so payable by way of the return, with or without interest thereon or any other addition thereto, of subscriptions to a provident fund;
(18) \xe2\x80\x9cProclamation of Emergency\xe2\x80\x9d means a Proclamation issued under clause (1) of article 352;
(19) \xe2\x80\x9cpublic notification\xe2\x80\x9d means a notification in the Gazette of India, or, as the case may be, the Official Gazette of a State;
(20) \xe2\x80\x9crailway\xe2\x80\x9d does not include\xe2\x80\x94
(a) a tramway wholly within a municipal area, or
(b) any other line of communication wholly situate in one State and declared by Parliament by law not to be a railway;
(23) \xe2\x80\x9cSchedule\xe2\x80\x9d means a Schedule to this Constitution;
(24) \xe2\x80\x9cScheduled Castes\xe2\x80\x9d means such castes, races or tribes or parts of or groups within such castes, races or tribes as are deemed under article 341 to be Scheduled Castes for the purposes of this Constitution;
(25) \xe2\x80\x9cScheduled Tribes\xe2\x80\x9d means such tribes or tribal communities or parts of or groups within such tribes or tribal communities as are deemed under article 342 to be Scheduled Tribes for the purposes of this Constitution;
(26) \xe2\x80\x9csecurities\xe2\x80\x9d includes stock;
(27) \xe2\x80\x9csub-clause\xe2\x80\x9d means a sub-clause of the clause in which the expression occurs;
(28) \xe2\x80\x9ctaxation\xe2\x80\x9d includes the imposition of any tax or impost, whether general or local or special, and \xe2\x80\x9ctax\xe2\x80\x9d shall be construed accordingly;
(29) \xe2\x80\x9ctax on income\xe2\x80\x9d includes a tax in the nature of an excess profits tax;
(29A) \xe2\x80\x9ctax on the sale or purchase of goods\xe2\x80\x9d includes\xe2\x80\x94
(a) a tax on the transfer, otherwise than in pursuance of a contract, of property in any goods for cash, deferred payment or other valuable consideration;
(b) a tax on the transfer of property in goods (whether as goods or in some other form) involved in the execution of a works contract;
(c) a tax on the delivery of goods on hire-purchase or any system of payment by installments;
(d) a tax on the transfer of the right to use any goods for any purpose (whether or not for a specified period) for cash, deferred payment or other valuable consideration;
(e) a tax on the supply of goods by any unincorporated association or body of persons to a member thereof for cash, deferred payment or other valuable consideration;
(f) a tax on the supply, by way of or as part of any service or in any other manner whatsoever, of goods, being food or any other article for human consumption or any drink (whether or not intoxicating), where such supply or service, is for cash, deferred payment or other valuable consideration, and such transfer, delivery or supply of any goods shall be deemed to be a sale of those goods by the person making the transfer, delivery or supply and a purchase of those goods by the person to whom such
transfer, delivery or supply is made;
(30) \xe2\x80\x9cUnion territory\xe2\x80\x9d means any Union territory specified in the First Schedule and includes any other territory comprised within the territory of India but not specified in that Schedule.
